opaque /əʊˈpeɪk/

1. ADJ If an object or substance is opaque , you cannot see through it. 不透明的 

例： You can always use opaque glass if you need to block a street view. 如果你需要挡住外面的街景，你随时可以使用不透明玻璃。 

2. ADJ If you say that something is opaque , you mean that it is difficult to understand. 难理解的 

例： ...the opaque language of the inspector's reports. …检查员报告中晦涩难懂的语言。

